bout what’s actually useful to add!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, or environment/system property is required for meaningful coverage of org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1. The resolved artifact only depends on scala-library and typesafe-config, and normal actor-system/Props/serialization/dispatcher coverage can run in-process. The observed failure is caused by stale tests using removed deprecated classic TypedActor APIs, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Pekko 2.0.0-M1 removed many deprecated APIs; org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedActorExtension, and TypedProps are absent from the 2.0.0-M1 actor jar, so tests must not reuse those 1.1.5 coverage paths.\",\n    \"If generated tests intentionally exercise the async DNS default-nameserver fallback, that path reflects on sun.net.dns.ResolverConfiguration and may require --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED for JVM/native runs; this is optional path-specific setup, not required for baseline actor coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0259b73581f20398016a42859392a4819080f8364e05e71489\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1311, "output": 780, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38443, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782744454814, "responseId": "resp_0259b73581f20398016a4285874e10819087ea2d8efff37099"}}
